<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="525" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6670498" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6670498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6670498/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="525" targetBox="[1373,1964,1017,1431]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1988,2581,1009,1432]" pageId="6" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1988,2164,1127,1156]" pageId="6" pageNumber="525">Distribution.</emphasis>
New Guinea, restricted to Arfak Mts in the Bird's Head (= Vogelkop) Peninsula in West Papua Province, Indonesia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="525" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1988,2581,1009,1432]" lastBlockId="6.[1374,2580,1442,1866]" pageId="6" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1988,2234,1280,1313]" pageId="6" pageNumber="525">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body c.21-23 cm, tail c.21-25 cm; weight 244-305 g. Arfak Ring-tailed Possums have a relatively uniform orange-brown pelage and lack dorsal stripes and facial markings. Patch of pale fur, followed by darker fur, occurs behind ears.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1375,2397,1482,1511]" pageId="6" pageNumber="525" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1374,2580,1442,1866]" box="[1375,2397,1482,1511]" pageId="6" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1375,1486,1482,1511]" pageId="6" pageNumber="525">Habitat.</emphasis>
